# define colors
# pink = c('#980043',"#DD1C77","#C994C7","#E7E1Ef")

pink = c('#980043',"#C994C7","#E7E1Ef")
blue = c('#08519c',"#9ecae1","#deebf7")
green = c('#006d2c','#a1d99b','#e5f5e0')
yellow = c('#ff9900','#ffff00','#ffff99')
col_list = list(pink,blue,green,yellow)

#color = c("#FF9933","#3399CC","#009900","#CC0099") # old color

# set some useful lists of variables
dom_list = c('high','med','low')
var_list = c('communicationdomain_totalb', 'livingskillsdomain_totalb', 'socializationdomain_totalb')
title_list = c('communication', 'livingskills', 'socialization')

# initialize some other useful variables
title = title 
data2use = data[data$TR_TS=="TR",]
plt_tr <- list()


# looping on VABS variables to 
for (j in (1:3)){
  #define varible, color to use and titels to the plots
  var2use = var_list[j]
  col_name = col_list[j]
  color = col_list[[j]] 
  title = title_list[j]
  
  p = ggplot(data = data2use, 
             aes_string(x = 'clust_dom',
                        y = var2use,
                        color='clust_dom')) 
  p = p + geom_jitter() + geom_boxplot(fill = NA, colour = "#000000", outlier.shape = NA)
  p = p + scale_colour_manual(values = color)
  p = p + guides(colour = FALSE)
  p = p + xlab("") + ylab("")
  p = p + ggtitle(title_list[j]) 
  p = p + theme_bw() 
  p = p + theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 0.5))
  ## changed here
  p = p + theme(axis.text.x = element_text(face="bold", size=10))
  p = p + theme(axis.text.y = element_text(face="bold", size=10))
  p = p + scale_y_continuous( limits=c(10, 120))
  p = p + theme(axis.text=element_text(size=10),
                axis.title=element_text(size=8,face="bold"))
  
  print(p)
  # evantually save the plot
  #ggsave(paste(plot_path,'/',db_type,'_total_',var2use,".pdf", sep=""))
  plt_tr[[j]] = p
}

check cluster significance - run sigclust

#data
umap_datapath = file.path(work_dir,"results")
plot_path = file.path(work_dir,"plot")
filename = "UMAP_values_VABSold_280722.csv"
data <- read.csv(file.path(umap_datapath,filename), header=TRUE)
colnames(data)= c('subjectkey','UMAP_1','UMAP_2','TR_TS','cluster')


# run sigclust
# set option
nreps_sim = 10000
nreps_sigclust_repeat = 10000

data$cluster =factor(data$cluster, levels = c("2",'0','1'))
# run sigclust on train
data2use_tr = data %>% filter(TR_TS=="tr") %>% select(UMAP_1,UMAP_2,cluster)
rseo_sigclust_res_train = sigclust(data2use_tr[,c("UMAP_1","UMAP_2")],
                             nsim = nreps_sim, nrep = nreps_sigclust_repeat,
                             labflag = 1, 
                             label = data2use_tr[,"cluster"],
                             icovest=2)
p_train = ggplot(data=data2use_tr, aes(x=UMAP_1,y=UMAP_2)) +
    geom_density_2d_filled() + 
    geom_point(data=data2use_tr, aes(colour=cluster), alpha = 0.3,size = 0.5)+ggtitle('train')+ 
    scale_y_continuous( limits=c(-11, 11)) + scale_x_continuous(limits=c(-7,5))  + theme_bw() 
p_train
## Warning: Removed 56 rows containing non-finite values (stat_density2d_filled).
## Warning: Removed 56 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

#rseo_sigclust_res_train
p_val_train = (sum(rseo_sigclust_res_train@simcindex<=rseo_sigclust_res_train@xcindex)+1)/(nreps_sim+1)
p_val_train
## [1] 9.999e-05
# run sigclust on test
data2use_ts = data %>% filter(TR_TS=="ts") %>% select(UMAP_1,UMAP_2,cluster)
rseo_sigclust_res_test = sigclust(data2use_ts[,c("UMAP_1","UMAP_2")],
                             nsim = nreps_sim, nrep = nreps_sigclust_repeat,
                             labflag = 1, 
                             label = data2use_ts[,"cluster"],
                             icovest=2)
#data2use_ts =  data[,c('UMAP_1','UMAP_2','cluster')]

p_test = ggplot(data=data2use_ts, aes(x=UMAP_1,y=UMAP_2)) +
    geom_density_2d_filled() + 
    geom_point(data=data2use_ts, aes(colour=cluster), alpha = 0.3,size = 0.5)+ggtitle('validation') + 
    scale_y_continuous( limits=c(-11, 11)) + scale_x_continuous(limits=c(-7,5))  + theme_bw() 
p_test
## Warning: Removed 28 rows containing non-finite values (stat_density2d_filled).
## Warning: Removed 28 rows containing missing values (geom_point).

#rseo_sigclust_res_test
p_val_test = (sum(rseo_sigclust_res_test@simcindex<=rseo_sigclust_res_test@xcindex)+1)/(nreps_sim+1)
p_val_test
## [1] 9.999e-05
# save outputs
umap_tr_ts = ggarrange(p_train, p_test, nrow=1, common.legend = TRUE, legend="bottom")
